function Start(idActor, idActorDetector)
	if (idActor ~= ID_Brute[1]) then
		if Events.MonsterIsHuman(idActor) then
			--Make sure the monster hasn't been affected by the bell recently
			if (Hydra.BuffIsOnActor(S_POWER_GOTO_BELL, "CANT_BE_ATTRACTED", idActor) == false) then
				-- Track monsters that enter the bell radius
				-- Merge ai state onto them that causes them to walk over and stand infront of the bell
				-- add them to an actor group so if they are attacked the aistate is removed
				T_AtractedMonsters[#T_AtractedMonsters+1] = idActor
				Hydra.ActorMergeAIState(idActor, S_AISTATE_GOTO_BELL, idActor, 0)
				Hydra.ActorAddToGroup(idActor, "OWV_Drowned_MonstersInTrance")
			end
		end
	end
end

function Start(idActorDamager, idActorDamaged)
	Hydra.ActorRemoveMergedAIState(idActorDamaged, S_AISTATE_GOTO_BELL)
	Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget("OWV_Drowned_MoveToBell", "CANT_BE_ATTRACTED", idActorDamaged)
end

function Start(idActor, fRange, idActorDetector)
	if Hydra.ActorIsValid(ID_Spawner) then
		Hydra.ActorTriggerSpawnerUpdate(ID_Spawner)
	end
end

unk_9c63f9d.value:
Hydra.Wait(0.3)
for i = 1, #T_AtractedMonsters do
	if (Hydra.ActorIsValid(T_AtractedMonsters[i])) then
		Hydra.ActorRemoveMergedAIState(T_AtractedMonsters[i], S_AISTATE_GOTO_BELL)
	end
end
OWC_SMP_CHECK()

T_AtractedMonsters = {}

-- setup brute to hit bell
Hydra.ActorMergeAIState(ID_Brute[1], S_AISTATE_HIT_BELL, ID_Brute[1], 0)
Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(S_POWER_GOTO_BELL, "ATTRACTING_ACTORS", ID_Bell[1])
